Modify the Persistent SSE `useEffect` in `apps/client/src/layers/features/chat/model/use-chat-session.ts` to respect the `enableCrossClientSync` store value.

## Read Toggle from Store

Add after the existing `const selectedCwd = useAppStore((s) => s.selectedCwd);` (around line 115):

```typescript
const enableCrossClientSync = useAppStore((s) => s.enableCrossClientSync);
```

## Guard the SSE Effect

The Persistent SSE effect is around line 308. Currently it has:

```typescript
useEffect(() => {
  if (!sessionId) return;
  if (isStreaming) return;

  const clientIdParam = transport.clientId ? `?clientId=${encodeURIComponent(transport.clientId)}` : '';
  const url = `/api/sessions/${sessionId}/stream${clientIdParam}`;
  const eventSource = new EventSource(url);
  // ... event listeners ...
  return () => {
    eventSource.close();
  };
}, [sessionId, isStreaming, queryClient, transport.clientId]);
```

Add one early return after the `isStreaming` guard:

```typescript
if (!sessionId) return;
if (isStreaming) return;
if (!enableCrossClientSync) return;
```

Add `enableCrossClientSync` to the dependency array:

```typescript
}, [sessionId, isStreaming, queryClient, transport.clientId, enableCrossClientSync]);
```

## Behavior

- When `enableCrossClientSync` changes from `true` to `false`, React runs the cleanup (closes EventSource), then re-runs the effect (hits early return). No stale closure risk.
- When toggled back to `true`, the EventSource connection is re-established.
- Presence info (`presenceInfo`) stays null when disabled, so the `ClientsItem` presence badge naturally disappears (already guarded by `!!presenceInfo && presenceInfo.clientCount > 1`).
- `sync_update` events stop arriving, so no `queryClient.invalidateQueries()` calls occur.

## Acceptance Criteria

- When `enableCrossClientSync` is `false`, no EventSource connection is created
- When `enableCrossClientSync` is `true` (default), EventSource works as before
- Toggling takes effect immediately without page reload
- No changes to `ChatStatusSection` needed (presence badge disappears naturally)

